ST. PETERSBURG — A motorcyclist and a truck driver crashed on Tyrone Boulevard Monday afternoon, killing the motorcyclist. The truck driver was towing a landscaping equipment trailer south on Tyrone Boulevard around 2:28 p.m. Monday. The driver turned east near Winchester Road North, crossing in front of a northbound motorcyclist, and the two vehicles collided, St. Petersburg police said in a media release. The motorcyclist died at the scene. The man’s name will be released once his family is notified, police said. The truck driver, who was uninjured, remained at the scene and is cooperating with investigators, police said. Tyrone Boulevard is closed from 13th Avenue to Winchester Road North for the investigation, St. Petersburg police said. This is a developing story. Stay with tampabay.com for updates.